comment: Smith (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and does not affect Evans' (NOP) ability to secure the entry pass as the two players make incidental contact with one another.
LATR shows that Cunningham (NOP) maintains legal guarding position and that James (CLE) makes incidental contact with him during his driving layup attempt.
RATR and RHH shows that Jefferson (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Holiday's (NOP) driving layup attempt.
Davis (NOP) and Smith (CLE) make incidental contact with one another while chasing after the loose ball.
Davis (NOP) gains possession prior to the 24 Second clock expiring on Cleveland's previous possession.
Davis (NOP) maintains legal guarding position as he defends James' (CLE) drive and layup attempt.
RHH shows that Love (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Evans' (NOP) driving shot attempt.
Evans (NOP) commits a take foul on James (CLE).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined that the foul committed by Evans (NOP) did not meet the criteria for a clear path foul.
Cunningham (NOP) maintains legal guarding position as he defends James' (CLE) drive and jump shot attempt.
Thompson (CLE) sets the screen on Holiday (NOP) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Holiday (NOP) commits a take foul as Thompson (CLE) goes up for the layup attempt.
James (CLE) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Cunningham (NOP) maintains legal guarding position as he defends James' (CLE) driving layup attempt. Any contact on the play is initiated by James.
Love (CLE) does not go through Anderson's (NOP) space and the contact is incidental.
Smith (CLE) makes contact with Davis (NOP) that affects his ability to secure the entry pass.
Smith (CLE) and Davis (NOP) briefly engage and separate.
Dellavedova (CLE) and Thompson (CLE) trap Evans (NOP) in the backcourt, but Evans is awarded a timeout prior to any illegal contact.
Smith (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Davis' (NOP) post up and turnaround shot attempt.
Davis (NOP) legally contests Smith's (CLE) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
RATR shows that Thompson (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Evans' (NOP) driving shot attempt.
Dellavedova (CLE) commits a take foul on Holiday (NOP).
James (CLE) commits a take foul on Gordon (NOP).
